$interpreted: Nolva: Well... We've be waiting forever already... Is this definitely the right place? We're not meeting somewhere else, are we?
Hugo: This is the rendezvous point. But... it was the Head of the House of Serafin who made the arrangements. I don't trust him...
Nolva: But why would he want to help us in the first place? And why do we have to head north all of a sudden?
Hugo: Our only chance of resolving the source of all this calamity lies to the north. You were chosen for this, and I'm escorting you.
Nolva: ...If I asked you how you know all of this, you wouldn't tell me anything... would you?
Sun Patrolman: It's those two! They're wanted criminals!
Nolva: Oh, a patrol group! What good fortune...
Hugo: It's another trap?!
Sun Patrolman: After them! Don't let them get away!
Hugo: Follow me, I'll get us out of here...
???: —Make way, make way! Not my fault if anyone's hit!
Sun Patrolman: What the hell is this?!
Nolva: Eh?!
Hugo: Wait!
???: All goods collected, now let's step on it!
???: Phew~ That was fun. Nothing better than gunning it full throttle, let me tell ya!
???: Bwahaha, almost forgot about you back there.
???: Are you all right, lady? It's normal to feel nauseous the first time. Stick with it a few more times, and I can guarantee you'll fall in love with the reckless feeling...
Nolva: Gah~ ahh...
???: Pffahaha, for real?! You were asleep the whole time? Damn, that's crazy~
Nolva: No, I... Waverlyde thought I was in danger, so...
Nolva: Ah! No! Wait a moment... Who are you...?
???: Oops, almost forgot to introduce myself. I'm your point man.
Dan Shan: The most professional, most reliable leader of Dan Shan's Flying Carriage Co.—Dan Shan, that's me.
Nolva: Flying... Carriage...
Nolva: You mean you're the expert smuggler who's gonna take us to the East?!
Dan Shan: Yup, you can just call me Dan Shan though~ Or how about...
Dan Shan: The Hunky King of Carriages, for short~
Nolva: (...Why am I not surprised that this guy's a criminal?)
Nolva: ...Uh, I'll just call you Mister Dan Shan...
Dan Shan: As you please. Just do what feels comfortable.
Dan Shan: Sorry about what happened earlier. I've no idea why the patrolmen changed their rounds this time. I thought it'd be best to snatch you out of there first and explain later~
Nolva: Ah, so it wasn't a trap after all...
Dan Shan: I apologize for the error. I hope this won't damage our reputation. Hows about I give you a free commission to make up for it? Yours to use anytime, anyplace.
Nolva: Th-thank you... That won't be necessary just now...
Nolva: Is my companion coming with us? I don't see him anywhere. I wonder what happened...
Dan Shan: Don't worry about him, it's been enough of a thrill just dealing with you already.
Dan Shan: Forget about anyone else! Just enjoy the speed, the passion of the Flying Carriage!
Nolva: Wait, hyaah—!
Exhausted Patrolman: S... st... stop...
Dan Shan: Wow~ You're really tenacious, huh?
Dan Shan: Seems like trouble follows you wherever you go, lady.
Nolva: I'm s-sorry... I didn't mean to bother you...
Dan Shan: Bwahaha... Not at all, I live for this. Somebody's gotta take all those life-endangering jobs, might as well be me~
Dan Shan: And like I said, Dan Shan's Flying Carriage Co. are experts in such matters!
Nolva: B-but that's a swamp ahead of us... We'll never make it...
Dan Shan: Oh, you ain't seen nothin'~ Wanna see this baby's true power?
Dan Shan: Let's do this—Super cross-country mode, engage!
Nolva: Amazing! The wheels are changing!
Dan Shan: I know, I know, I'm amazing. Just remember to hold on tight!
Exhausted Patrolman: After them!
Panicked Patrolman: But Captain, it's a bog?!
Exhausted Patrolman: So what! In the name of the Sun, we can't let 'em escape!
Panicked Patrolman: I can't... feel the bottom... My feet.... My feet are stuck!
Exhausted Patrolman: Don't you dare give up! ...Ughh...
Dan Shan: Heh, amateurs... I've gotta hand it to them though, they're real dedicated...
Nolva: ...Mr. Dan Shan, about that free ride you mentioned... May I use use it now?
Dan Shan: Wh-whaat?! You're not telling me you wanna... go back and rescue those hot-blooded morons, are you?
Nolva: Please, will you do it?
Dan Shan: If you're gonna throw a valuable freebie away, that's on you. But those soldiers were coming after you!
Dan Shan: ...I mean, try reading the room, maybe?
Nolva: I know that. But I won't stand by and watch them drown, either. They're just doing their jobs, after all...
Dan Shan: It's always the goody-goodies who get themselves into the biggest trouble.
Dan Shan: —Hell, kiddo, it's your life on the line.
Dan Shan: You're free to use your commission however you like! As a matter of honor and pride, I'll do all I can to see you through this in one piece.
Nolva: ...Mr. Dan Shan... You're a good man...
Dan Shan: Bwahaha... I'm not good for nothin'. But the customer is always right!
